    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        - Adults 18 - 90 yrs.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Suspected or confirmed coagulopathy (including current treatment with anticoagulants
             or antiplatelet agents).

          -  Surgical blood loss volume &lt; 200 ml.

          -  Requirement for surgical gauzes during surgery, including conversion to open surgical
             techniques.

          -  Transfusion of red blood cells (RBCs) during the perioperative period.

          -  Significant postoperative bleeding (&gt; 50 ml in surgical drains) or any other type of
             significant blood loss.

          -  Fluid infusions or vasoactive drugs after the first 24 postoperative hours.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
